[20:08:08] Step 4: Full details for int_sales_orders_with_campaign...
[20:08:14]   Model: int_sales_orders_with_campaign
[20:08:14]   Description:
[20:08:14]     One row per sales order, enriched with campaign attribution metadata. Built by left-joining stg_ecom__sales_orders to conversion events from stg_ecom__email_campaigns. Grain: one row per sales_order_id. Campaign columns (campaign_id, customer_segment, product_category, ad_strategy) are null when the order was not driven by a campaign. is_campaign_conversion is the key flag for campaign ROI analysis. This model feeds int_sales_order_with_customers, which powers the Snowsight sales dashboard.
[20:08:14]   Columns (8):
[20:08:14]     - sales_order_id: Primary key. Unique identifier for the sales order. Inherited from stg_ecom__sales_orders.

[20:08:14]     - customer_id: Customer who placed the order. Foreign key to stg_adventure_db__customers.customer_id.

[20:08:14]     - order_date: Timestamp when the order was placed, in UTC.
[20:08:14]     - campaign_id: Composite campaign identifier (customer_segment~product_category~ad_strategy) from the attributed campaign conversion event. Null if this order was not attributed to a campaign.

[20:08:14]     - customer_segment: Customer segment targeted by the campaign. Parsed from campaign_id. Null for non-campaign orders.

[20:08:14]     - product_category: Product category promoted by the campaign. Parsed from campaign_id. Null for non-campaign orders.

[20:08:14]     - ad_strategy: Advertising strategy used by the campaign. Parsed from campaign_id. Null for non-campaign orders.

[20:08:14]     - is_campaign_conversion: 1 if this order is attributed to an email campaign conversion event, 0 otherwise. Primary flag for measuring campaign-driven revenue.

[20:08:14]   Depends on:
[20:08:14]     <- stg_ecom__sales_orders
[20:08:14]     <- stg_ecom__email_campaigns
